        "whyItMatters": "A fund reporting improving IRR with flat DPI is marking up unrealized positions. The gains exist only on paper until exits confirm them. Cambridge Associates benchmark data shows median DPI for 2015–2018 vintage buyout funds at year 8 in the 0.9–1.2x range - a fund materially below that range with strong reported IRR deserves specific scrutiny.",
