        "whyItMatters": "A year-3 VC fund with −15% net IRR and a year-3 buyout fund with −5% net IRR are not comparably distressed - the VC fund's J-curve is structurally deeper and longer. Interpreting early-year VC metrics using buyout timelines leads to premature negative judgments about VC managers and the strategy.",
        "sourceNote": "J-curve variation across PE strategies: CAIA Association Level II, private equity and venture capital performance chapters; Cambridge Associates Private Equity and Venture Capital Benchmark Commentary."
