        "title": "What portfolio-level value creation data can and cannot tell you",
        "content": "**What it can tell you:**\n- Whether EBITDA growth is consistent across the portfolio or driven by one or two outliers - consistency is a much stronger skill signal than outlier performance\n- Whether the GP's returns are primarily operational (EBITDA growth) vs. financial engineering (multiple expansion + debt paydown) - the mix tells you about forward repeatability\n- Whether the GP's bolt-on strategy is genuinely value-accretive - by comparing acquisition multiples to the portfolio exit multiple, you can assess whether bolt-ons created or destroyed value per EBITDA dollar\n- Whether operating partner involvement is substantive - deal-level data that shows specific initiatives with measurable EBITDA impact at specific portfolio companies is verifiable; generic claims are not"
