        "content": "Day 18 introduced stale marks and smoothing at the private-markets level. Day 24 then established that valuation is a governance system, not just a number. Day 33 now integrates those ideas into the central allocator question for venture: how should you interpret marks when most of the portfolio is unrealized and the available price signals are partial, structured, delayed, or security-specific?\nThis changes venture performance is often unrealized for long periods. The learner is not being asked to become a valuation accountant. The goal is narrower and more practical: build the ability to rank valuation evidence, identify when last-round pricing is misleading, and attach an appropriate confidence level to venture NAV rather than accepting it mechanically."
