        "content": "For a successor-fund decision, growth equity should be judged less on broad brand quality and more on whether the GP has shown repeatable discipline around price, governance, and exit dependency. Five questions are high value.\n**1. Does the track record still work after stripping out multiple expansion?** If not, the historical edge may be more market-driven than process-driven.\n**2. Are the best outcomes concentrated in one market regime or one subsector?** A strategy built on 2020 to 2021 software re-rating is not the same as a cycle-robust franchise.\n**3. Are minority rights actually usable?** Board access, information rights, financing consents, and sale influence matter more than generic partnership language.\n**4. Is the GP drifting toward auction-heavy, larger deals?** Scale can turn a previously nimble growth strategy into an expensive late-stage strategy with less margin for error.\n**5. Does the current pipeline still match the original edge?** If sourcing now depends on broad intermediary exposure, the strategy may have matured out of its original advantage."
