        "content": "The GP says: 'Our private credit strategy offers downside protection, contractual cash flows, and attractive risk-adjusted returns.' That may all be directionally true. It is also far too broad for allocator use. A private-credit-fluent allocator wants to know: what kind of credit is this, what exactly is underwriting the loan, where does repayment really come from, what covenant protection exists, how much of the return is carry versus fees or leverage, and what happens when the borrower cannot refinance on schedule?"
