        "content": "The GP says: 'We focus on distressed and special situations credit to capture outsized returns when markets dislocate.' That is directionally true, but it is still too broad for allocator use. A distressed-credit-fluent allocator wants to know whether the manager is buying stressed paper for spread, positioning around a fulcrum security to gain control, providing rescue financing with bespoke protections, or underwriting a formal restructuring pathway. The critical question is not only what yield or discount the manager is buying."
