        "content": "The GP says: 'We focus on asset-based finance and specialty credit. The deals are self-amortizing and overcollateralized, so the strategy is defensively positioned.' That framing is too shallow for allocator underwriting. In ABF, the real questions are what sits in the borrowing base, who verifies eligibility, how advance rates are set, what happens when servicer performance weakens, how concentrated the obligors really are, and whether the manager has the data stack to see deterioration before it becomes a realized loss."
