        "content": "The GP says: 'We bought a high-quality asset at an attractive cap rate and will create value through active management.' A property-literate allocator should immediately translate that into harder questions: how much of NOI is in place today, when major leases roll, what capex is needed to defend occupancy, what refinancing assumptions are embedded, and how much of the equity case depends on an exit cap rate and loan market that may not be available when the debt matures."
