        "content": "Day 47 taught the learner to classify private-real-estate strategies correctly. Day 48 asks a different question: once the style label is set, what actually makes a property a good or bad investment? The answer is not a headline cap rate. It is the interaction of rent-roll durability, expense realism, capex burden, leverage, and the availability of refinance or sale liquidity when the business plan is tested.\nThe allocator should underwrite a property through three linked lenses:\n- **income durability:** how much cash flow is contractual and defendable today\n- **execution burden:** what leasing, redevelopment, or capex work must go right\n- **capital-markets dependence:** whether the property can refinance or exit if rates, values, or lender appetite move the wrong way"
